---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="About" sideBarActiveItemID="about">
  <main class="md:flex md:justify-center">
    <article class="prose prose-lg max-w-[750px] w-full">

      <div class="pb-8 mt-5" style="border-left: 2px solid #F5A623; padding-left: 24px;">
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-4">About Me</h1>

        <p>
          Hello there! I’m Josh Crotty, currently pursuing an MSc in Mathematical
          Modelling & Machine Learning at University College Cork (UCC). I previously
          completed an undergraduate degree in Software Systems Development at SETU,
          where I built a strong foundation in software engineering, data science, and
          modern development practices.
        </p>
      </div>

    <figure class="not-prose my-8">
      <img
        src="/about/ucc_quad.jpg"
        loading="lazy"
        alt="The Quadrangle at University College Cork"
        class="w-full max-h-[400px] object-cover rounded-md"
      />
      <figcaption class="text-center text-sm opacity-60 mt-2">
        The Quadrangle at University College Cork (UCC).
      </figcaption>
    </figure>

      <p>
        My main interests centre around building scalable intelligent systems,
        particularly where data science, machine learning, and software engineering
        intersect. I have a strong interest in healthcare applications of AI,
        especially how data analysis and machine learning can contribute to solving
        meaningful problems.
      </p>

      <p>
        I also enjoy technical writing and knowledge sharing, which is one of the
        motivations behind this blog. I regularly write about concepts I’m learning,
        projects I’m working on, and ideas around AI, software, and applied
        mathematics.
      </p>

      <p>
        During my undergraduate final year, I developed a cloud based deep learning
        system for detecting signs of Alzheimer’s disease from MRI imaging. This work
        was recognised with the Sun Life Academic Award and the DCH Consulting Award
        for Charitable & Sustainable Thinking.
      </p>

      <p>
        Looking ahead, I hope to move into industry or research & development within
        healthcare AI, contributing to systems that have real impact.
      </p>

    </article>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>